  "CGAL::Interval_skip_list": {
    "kind": "class",
    "name": "CGAL::Interval_skip_list",
    "brief": "The class Interval_skip_list is a dynamic data structure that allows to find all members of a set of intervals that overlap a point.",
    "detailed": "Implementation The insertion and deletion of a segment in the interval skip list takes expected time $O(\\log^2 n)$ , if the segment endpoints are chosen from a continuous distribution. A stabbing query takes expected time $O(\\log n)$ , and finding all intervals that contain a point takes expected time $O(\\log n + k)$ , where $ k$ is the number of intervals. The implementation is based on the code developed by Eric N. Hansen.",
